{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"66ac0a03-60f4-4b59-b2c6-eff269f2f148","content":"Two things change with MTP's **treenode-filter** syntax:\n\n| Concept | VSTest (v2) | MTP (v3) |\n|---|---|---|\n| Name contains | `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` | `/**/*IntegrationTests*` (glob path) |\n| Trait match | `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (bracket notation) |\n| AND | `&` between expressions | Combine inline |\n\n**Your new CI command:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nWhen using `dotnet test` (not the raw executable), `--filter` is also accepted and forwarded as the treenode filter:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nThe glob `/**/*IntegrationTests*` matches any test whose path contains \"IntegrationTests\" at any depth, and `[Category=Smoke]` restricts to tests with that trait.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7f4612a9-8cf1-4edf-b4f9-2276e1a3d287","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is using xUnit.net v3 with Microsoft Testing Platform (MTP). With MTP, `dotnet test --filter` changes significantly:\n\n1. **MTP uses `--filter` differently** - The VSTest filter syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke`) doesn't work the same way with MTP.\n\n2. Key changes in xUnit v3 with MTP:\n   - The `--filter` option uses a different syntax\n   - Trait filtering uses different property names\n   - The `&` operator and `~` (contains) operator syntax changes\n\nWith MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform), the filter syntax changes:\n\n\n- `FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests` still works but the property might be different\n- `Category=Smoke` doesn't work directly since MTP accesses traits differently than VSTest does\n\nWhen using `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, the test executable becomes standalone, and while `dotnet test` still works, the filter property names change significantly. In MTP, traits aren't accessed via `Category` directly like they are in VSTest—xUnit v3 with MTP uses a different approach for trait filtering.\n\nThe core issue is that `dotnet test --filter` now uses MTP filter syntax instead of VSTest syntax, which means operators like `~` (contains) and the way logical operators work may differ, and the tree-node filter syntax becomes relevant depending on how MTP is configured. The treenode filter syntax in MTP combines path patterns with property filters using brackets, so I can filter by name with `/**/*IntegrationTests*` and add trait filtering like `[Category=Smoke]` to get `/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]`. When using `dotnet test`, the `--filter` argument gets passed through to MTP as `--treenode-filter`, though I should verify the exact behavior here since there might be some translation happening between the two interfaces. I need to clarify that when `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner` is enabled, the `dotnet test --filter` argument gets converted to MTP's `--treenode-filter` syntax, so users need to use the treenode filter format instead of the standard dotnet test filter syntax.","outputTokens":1452,"requestId":"CFC7:335471:5C96A13:67E1E20:69EC1018"},"id":"b07ccc06-dedc-40b6-9274-1c89818cd5e4","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:52:06.291Z","parentId":"708d684d-4ca6-4372-abfe-34dcd518a150"}
